    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p>Part b: <bibl><ptr target="#CIG"/> <citedRange>5169</citedRange> (Franz)</bibl> (part), from 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#pacho1827"/>, pl. <citedRange>65, 2</citedRange></bibl> and copy by [Negri], Sardinian consul in Tripoli (n. 6); 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SGDI"/> <citedRange>4864</citedRange> (Blass)</bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cassels1955"/>, p. <citedRange>34</citedRange>, tomb S1</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>008260</citedRange></bibl>;
                    part a: unpublished before <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>008260</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
                <p>Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2020c"/>, pp. <citedRange>316-317</citedRange>, n. 3 and fig. 3a-b</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2020"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.19</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-66084"><name nymRef="#Φίλων"><milestone unit="fragment" n="a"/>Φί<milestone unit="fragment" n="b"/>λων</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63470"><name nymRef="#Δᾶμις" type="patronymic"><milestone unit="fragment" n="a"/>Δά<milestone unit="fragment" n="b"/>μιος</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p> Philôn fils de Damis.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p> Philon son of Damis.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p> Philon figlio di Damis.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>فيلون بن داميوس</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Although having got from both origins two different copies, Franz (followed by Blass) brought together this inscription and <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr008250</ref>, 
                    just because they seemed to bear the same names, which in fact are both very frequent at Cyrene and there is no need to consider both bases as one and the same. Moreover,
                    there is no clue that they belong to the same tomb.</p>
                <p>We know since Cassels that fragment b was to be seen in the courtyard of tomb S1. Excavations conducted in 2009 by O. Menozzi and the archaeological mission of the 
                    University of Chieti in that tomb brought to light fragment a.</p>
                
            </div></body>
    </text>
